# EvolveX — Cursor AI Context

## Project
Self-modifying agent evolution system for the EvolveX hackathon.
Agents analyze their own performance, propose code mutations, validate in sandbox, and apply successful changes.

## Stack
- Python 3.11 + FastAPI — agent engine, evolution loop, sandbox execution
- Next.js 15 (App Router) + Tailwind — real-time evolution dashboard
- OpenAI API (Codex / GPT-4.1) — agent intelligence layer
- WebSockets — live dashboard updates

## Architecture
agents/
  base_agent.py       — Base agent class with benchmark + self-analysis
  performer.py        — Agent A: executes benchmark tasks
  analyzer.py         — Agent B: measures performance, identifies improvements
  modifier.py         — Agent C: proposes and applies code mutations

evolution/
  sandbox.py          — Isolated code execution environment
  checkpoint.py       — Save/restore agent states
  fitness.py          — Performance scoring and metrics
  loop.py             — Main evolution orchestrator

dashboard/            — Next.js real-time visualization
  src/app/            — App Router pages
  src/components/     — React components (EvolutionTree, MetricsChart, etc.)
  src/lib/            — WebSocket client, API helpers

## Key Patterns
- Agents NEVER modify themselves directly — all mutations go through sandbox.py first
- Every modification creates a checkpoint before applying
- Failed mutations auto-rollback to last checkpoint
- Fitness scores are the single source of truth for evolution decisions

## Do NOT
- Hardcode API keys — use .env
- Skip sandbox validation — all code runs in isolation first
- Skip checkpoint before mutation — rollback depends on it
